parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition coil can cause the engine to misfire, leading to poor engine performance, decreased fuel efficiency, and potentially causing damage to other engine components.
symptoms: Engine light comes on
excessive high voltage
rough idling
progressive ignition rough idling
spark knock or detonation.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the alternator can cause the battery to drain, leading to the vehicle stalling or shutting down, which can be a safety hazard, especially if it occurs while driving.
symptoms: Battery light comes on
vehicle shuts down
inability to start the vehicle
warning lights on the instrument panel flash.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electrical system issues can cause a range of problems, including stalling, shutting down, and difficulty starting the vehicle, which can be a safety hazard.
symptoms: Vehicle quits in traffic
battery and brake warning lights come on
instrument panel lights flash
difficulty starting the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Poor visibility of the instrument panel can make it difficult for the driver to monitor the vehicle's systems, which can be a safety hazard.
symptoms: Instrument panel is difficult to read in bright sunlight
becomes a "black hole" when trying to look at it with sunglasses on.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Rust Corrosion of Front Frame Tie Bar
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The rust corrosion of the front frame tie bar can lead to a loss of structural integrity, potentially causing the hood to pop open while driving or compromising front-end control in a collision.
symptoms: Rust perforation on the front frame tie bar
particularly near the center of the boxed frame member.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the air flow sensor can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to abnormal deceleration and stalling, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Loss of power
abnormal deceleration
stalling
and the illumination of the check engine light.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the catalytic converter can cause the vehicle to fail emissions tests, and potentially lead to further engine damage.
symptoms: Illumination of the check engine light
P0420 code
and failure to pass emissions tests.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine smoking and fire can cause damage to the vehicle and potentially lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Smoke coming from under the hood
engine fire.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the oxygen sensor can cause the vehicle to run poorly, leading to decreased performance and potentially causing damage to other engine components.
symptoms: Illumination of the check engine light
P0140 code
and excessive high voltage.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition coils can cause the vehicle to misfire, leading to decreased performance and potentially causing damage to other engine components.
symptoms: Illumination of the service engine soon light
misfiring
and the need to replace ignition coils.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition coil can cause the engine to misfire, leading to rough idling, decreased performance, and potential engine damage.
symptoms: The service engine light remains illuminated
the engine rough idles
the vehicle misfires
and the engine has a decreased performance.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front control arm can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The front control arm is rusted
the front control arm breaks
the vehicle pulls to one side
and the vehicle vibrates.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause extended stopping distances, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The brake pedal goes too far to the floor
the vehicle takes longer to stop
the rotors are warped or worn out
and the vehicle vibrates when braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to jerk or hesitate when shifting, leading to loss of control or accidents.
symptoms: The transmission stays in low gear too long
the transmission jerks when shifting
and the vehicle hesitates when accelerating.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the suspension and steering systems can cause the vehicle to vibrate or lose control, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle vibrates at high speeds
the steering wheel vibrates
and the vehicle pulls to one side.
